\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid5267124 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where did you live when you were first born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I was born in Queen Street. Farnworth. We were all born in Farnworth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Not all at Queen Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 That was your first home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, Queen Street was our first home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How long did you live there, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh was living there - I was - six when we left Queen
 Street. And I'll tell you why we left - why we left Queen Street. My father was moved to Bolton, he had to go to Bolton to work for the Royal Liver there and mother couldn't settle so she came back to Farnworth, fetched him back, and they lived in King S
treet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You went to King Street after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. From there we got a house in Church Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Still Farnworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. And from there they got a house in Prestoll Street. Yes. And from there we went to Vernon Street. Mother died in Vernon S
treet. And when mother died was all of us and I left that wasn't married. And we got - we came back to Prestoll Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where was the house you lived the longest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 The house in Prestoll Street, forty-seven years. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Can you tell me how many rooms there were in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 
Yes, only four and that in Prestoll Street because we had to leave Church Street on account mother got as she couldn't pay the rates and the rent. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 'Cos they got married and went from her -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 The children got married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, and we had to look after mother so she went in a smaller house to heap us along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where was the house you lived as a child the longest, all of you together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Prestoll Street, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And only four rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did you manage to sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well, see, I've had two little brothers then before, so there's only the one brother that went to the war, after that and most of them married so there was just enough room for the ones that weren't married, all girls, and th
en the others got married and left home, mother died of gall stones you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But when you were children how did you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well we had to do the best way we could. Boy and parents in one room with screens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You put screens across you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 All the girls in one room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Just the family lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No aunties or uncles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
No. No. No, just the family. Then we went to that house in Church because it's a bigger house - with a bath, so all our troubles were down there. Father had a large family and all getting married and then we had to leave for a less house with less rent.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Your father was an insurance agent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you know where he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He was born - was born in Hall Lane Farnworth. Yes. He was Farnworth, yes, yes. Me grandmother was a Farnworth woman. Yes. Farnworth.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was he always an insurance agent?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He never did part time work or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh. no. Just that - that was his sole job but he sold - 
he sold - he had a sideline, he sold pictures ea - to help his wage up. He sold different pictures and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where would he get the pictures from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well probably Manchester somewhere he used to go, he used to sell them for this firm and that was a si
deline to help his insurance money. My mother was a dressmaker and she always kept us nicely dressed and no one knew we were poor, and we were very poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was she from Farnworth too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She was Farnworth woman, yes. We were always nicely dressed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And your mother worked after she was married did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes, on the machine, all the time, soon as one baby was born she's back on the machine again. Yes, made a lovely wedding dress for five shilling. Yes. Yes. Mind you that was a long time ago. Fi
ve shillings - those were dresses those days you know, long trains too. She had a model. Yes, she had a - she had a model.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She used to take in sewing just from anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She used to take it in from anyone, yes, she had a - my father had a brass pl
ate on the door for his insurance and mother had a brass plate underneath for her dress - making. That's when we had a lot of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 So she'd be able to look after you even though she was working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes, she did but dad helped a lot I had one of the kindest fathers you could wish to have. A love, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Could you always talk to him about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He was beautiful. Kindness itself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He was. He always had one of us on his knee. Yes, it's a lovely memory. And I was only fifteen but I've never forgotten him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did he help your mother to look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Always - and wash up because she always had to keep her fingers pliable to sew you see. Yes. He used to do nearly all the housework. Yes. And cut all the bread and butter up, bring it through on a great big tray, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And he'd bath you and undress you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Help mother to bath us too and Saturday night, he never went - never - didn't drink, he didn't smoke, he used to spend all his time helping mother to get us ready for church on Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did he light fires and decorate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. No, he didn't decorate, no. He just did everything else and wouldn't decorate. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you ever see him repair shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, used to - yes, repair all our shoe
s. Clean them all, clean all our shoes. And we had a long dresser sideboard with white wood top with a white top on, mother used to cut all the food on, and on Sunday morning all the shoes used to be ready for us to change to put on to go to mass. Yes. Ye
s. Yes. And then mother and father used to go to the last mass. Mother was a Catholic but he wasn't. He never missed church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He used to go with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He used to go with her morning and afternoon on Sunday. Take us all with him, yes. But of course my mother and father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 didn't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10309615  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
tell us - and I didn't know he wasn't a Catholic 'til he was dying and he asked could he die in the Catholic faith. And they brought the priest and the priest wouldn't believe he wasn't a Catholic. He'd always seen him in church
 with my mother. With us all trailing behind him. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 We all went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was your mother affectionate too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Very. But she had not time to be as affectionate as me father because she was always busy but she did her best for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Could you take your worries to her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Oh yes. Oh yes. And I remember this from the family and I always remember us playing hopscotch with me brother at side and I've often the neighbours say, she's not like t
he others is she? Isn't she - little. And I went and I said to mother, mother, am I yours? She said, of course you are love, who says you're not? I said, oh she said I'm not like the others. She said I was more like a little rabbit. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 And me mother got hold of me, she said, you know, you're only a remnant, but you'll out task the lot and I am. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Isn't that strange? Father working in the - the Royal Liver he didn't start 'til he wanted, probably about half past nine or ten therefore he had time to get us some good breakfast ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He used to do breakfast for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes. Yes. Used to get the breakfast ready. I'll tell you what we used to have. A little bit of bacon, a tomato and a half an egg each. For our breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you have on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
And on Sunday had the same on Sunday. And mother used to make us a good dinner. And we had a nice tea. And then my father would - could play the piano - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 accordion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  and we had one of those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 accordions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  and after tea when we lived i
n Queen street, I can see it now, he used to sit down and have us all round him and he'd play the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 accordion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  while we sang.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was there anyone else who made music in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Agnes, me sister that died. She was - the eldest sister was a lovely singer. She was in the operas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did your mother sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Oh mother sang, yes, but not as good as me sister, me sister was also a trained singer in the end. Me mother - mother did afford to have her voice trained and eventually she got married and - started bringing a family up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did your mother ever have any paid help in the home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who did the washing, was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No, my eldest sister used to do it all do it between them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you were little who did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Mother and father between them. Yes. My father was more like a mother beside mother, yes. He was a good father. As gentle as a lamb.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Your mother would mend the clothes because she was a dressmaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh, she - she - she's go
t an old coat given to her, someone that's going to have a new coat made, she's unpicked that coat and made as a new coat, turned it, washed it and made u- a new coat out of it. I know one year that we were so poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When did you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
I don't think I had a new coat 'til I started work - at fourteen. No. I was always dressed right though - making things do. Made us lovely white dresses to walk in. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She'd buy the material and make them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. We always dressed nice then. And on Sundays we had all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 our}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  best clothes put on and put them away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You always had special clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Special clothes for Sunday, yes. Special shoes. Special shoes for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How often would you have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well - I'll tell you what mother used to do, she had a friend that kept a shoe shop. And instead of mother payin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
 the money for our shoes she used to do all the sewing. So we got our shoes that way. So she earned then before we wore them. Dad repaired them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have to help at home when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well I didn't do very - very much housework because I had four or five sisters other than myself. And I was always the smallest so I got more sympathy but I was one of the quickest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You didn't like being small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
I didn't like being small but I'll tell you what I did like - when they all used to be borrowing my mother's gloves and shoes and blouses to go out to a dance or anything like that I used to say, well - I'm glad I'm small, you can't wear mine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time on schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes. Always in bed nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Mother - my father put us to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What age did you start putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh - about - be about twelve or thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You shared the bedroom with your sisters didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where did you bath and how?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 We had a large tin bath and we used to have it in the kitchen. In front of the fire - kitchen fire. As one wa
s bathed she went upstairs to bed and another went in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How often was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Oh every week. Yes. But we had to wash our hands and face every night before we went to bed, we hadn't to go to bed with dirty face or hands. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When would you change your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Oh - I don't think we had a right lot to change you know, we never could have them you know, not a lot of clothes, no. We didn't have one special change, no, we got dirty we changed but my father used to see to that. Never sent us to
 school untidy or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where did you eat your meals in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
We had three rooms downstairs in King Street and we had them at our place called the dining room living room. We had a front room but they had a model on to fit the dresses on - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you ever go into another room when visitors came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You always used the dining room?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 This was at King Street when you were growing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where did your mother cook at King street then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 In the kitchen - in the - what we called the little off kitchen with the pantry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What equipment did she use, did she have gas or a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, we - we had a range in the kitchen. A black oven. And there was some good smells came out of it - we baked our own bread. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did she make jam or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, she didn't make jam but she baked all her own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh - she bought vegetables of course but she never bought anything fro
m shop, nothing out of a chip shop. Made all of her own - father did really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did he bake bread at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 My father kneaded the bread and mother used to watch it. She watched it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did they ever make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes. Yes. Jars of pickled cabbage. Oh yes, yes. I love a potato pie with a crust on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Tell me about your dinners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well, we used to come home from school twelve o'clock, my father's there. He used to have the dinner ready. Mother used to prepare the potato pie or wha
tever it was a pie in the oven. Mother used to put the crust and then we used to all sit round the table waiting for it to be served. Our father used to serve that, and he used to wash up after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who did he serve first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 The eldest came first, we all had our own place at table, you daren't take one another\rquote s place. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. We - we all had to have our special place and the eldest came first. Same at Christmas. When we were waiting to see what we had in our stocking, used to stand at the bottom of the s
tairs, the eldest came down first, we used to come down, down, down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Tell me about your dinners, you used to have rabbit pie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Rabbit pie and hot-pot and - what you call - a Lancashire potato pie with a crust on and kidney in. And sometimes a pa
n of broth on - on the front of the fire. Had herbs in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 So you were well fed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How many times a week would you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh - nearly every day if we could get it. - Now I'll tell you something about that. I was always on the sh
y side. My mother said to me one day she said, will you go to see Evans love, and ask him for a pound of rump steak. I thought that was very rude. So - I kept thinking, I don't like asking for rump steak. So I got to Mr Fielding and said, Mr Fielding, a p
ound of bottom steak for me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You thought bottom sounded better than rump?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I - did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10309615   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
 And at tea time we used to have a plain tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What would you call a plain tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Perhaps some ham, boiled ham or - and jam and bread and butte
r. Just a plain tea. About supper we used to have a drink of milk and up to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Oh special -we'd always have - have made apple pies and - cakes, jellies, fruit on Sunday and it was all on the table, it was a nice sight to se
e. My father used to go out of the kitchen with this tray with roses on, I can see it now, a big tray with all the bread and butter cut on. Big tray, yes, it had roses on. (father always put roses on tray with cut bread on Sunday).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did they ever make their own medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
No. Mother never did - no - she did - used to give us when we came home from school on Fridays she used to have a jug with lemonade in and a few - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 senna pods}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  in. And we didn't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did she ever make wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She made hop - hop beer and she made stout.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did she do that, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
She used to buy from Berry's drug store, she used to get the real malt in the jar to put in the stout, the beer. It used to smell lovely. We used to have a big mug wi
th it in - We used to have to keep taking the top off. Yes. And she used to make us drink the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Why I wonder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh because of the yeast - yes. To say they had very little education they were clever. They were clever in - many ways. And they cou
ld make a pound go then they're more - today they won't be able to make ten pounds go. She could make her money go without getting in debt. She used to say, it's nice to make ends meet but put a little mat on top. Save up. Yes. Always thought about that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did they grow vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, we had no garden. No, we had no garden, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember if your mother used to buy tinned fruit or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She never bought no - no, she wouldn't buy anything in tins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Not even tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
What she was meaning catcher No. No. And she wouldn't buy a cake out of the shops to put on the table. Sponge cake with all them eggs in. Big - in a big roasting tin. Yes. Toffee. Her own toffee. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She was busy wasn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 It was a busy life. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you get any extra meat from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh no. We're on the street really like we lived on the street like and there was no garden or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were you allowed to talk at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. We, were happy, and rowdy. And we all had to have our own place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you choose what you wanted to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, we had to ask for it. Ask for it. You daren't getup and take it off a - you had to ask mother for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Suppose you wanted the salt or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh we had to ask to pass it. Yes. You must'nt get your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have to clean your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No, she didn't force us to eat what we didn't like. You could ask for more if we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were you taught to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Taught table manners, yes. Yes, we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Could you bring books or toys of the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. No, not to the table. Bring them in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Could you leave the table when you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. We had to have permission to leave the table. Yes. We had our own place and we used to have to say please may I leave the table. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And all the family sat down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 All the family sat down together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And your father served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Served the meal, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When your younger brothers and sisters were to tiny to come to the table where did they sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well we had a lovely cradle, I remember that cradle. It was a beautiful wooden one. It belonged to my father's mother. Mothe
r used to drape it with curtain. Muslin curtain. And I remember sitting on the side of that - that - cradle rocking the baby. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But where did they sit before they were old enough to sit on a chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well they had a chair - a chair with a front on. Yes. Yes. A bib on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well mother and father and one of the others used to feed them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What age did they come to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh - about - four. About four years old, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters, had they any certain ways of bringing you up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 We aren't strike each other. Wasn't to lift your hand to one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Suppose someone hit you outside were you allowed to hit them back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. We used to go in and tell mother and She didn't like fighting, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What kind of people do you think they hoped you would grow up to be and what did they think was important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well - well to be good, that's all I can say. To be good. And not to be a
 nuisance to anyone. My mother - any trouble she always used to fetch us in. Always brought us in, yes. She uses to say, well - two blazes make a big fire. Make a big fire. Wait 'til one dies down. And mother. She was very wise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You thought the world of your mother obviously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. She's nice. Not much time really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you remember your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh I remember me father. Yes. He was a gentle - gentle man. A gentle gentleman, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did your family think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Never dare - we daren't swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 If grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. Not unless you were spoken to. My mother never sent us out of the room, we could sit quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Suppose you did anything wrong, who punished you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Father never
 punished us. He used to leave it to Mother, - Mother. Had a little strap but she didn't hit us with it. She used to hit the table with it. She'd threaten us and that was all. I got - remember that - remember being sent to bed once in my life and that was
 
for going down the market in the dark and I wanted to see this circus. And someone gave me tuppence for going an errand and me father had forbidden us to go so I went out and I saw the circus. And father stood at the gate waiting for me. So he said, where
 have you been? I said, I've been to the circus. He said, well didn't I tell you not to go on the market in the dark? He said, upstairs to bed without supper. So I just remember that, the first time father was ever angry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well mother fetch - mother sent him up with a cup of milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did you feel about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh I - I cried - oh I cried. Because my father had done it you see. Never lifted his hand to one of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Nor your mother either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, n
o. Oh no, no. Never lifted hand to one of us. And the only time I remember my father being angry because I disobeyed him with going on market in the dark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you think you received the ideas on how to behave from both your parents or do you think one played a more important part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well, I think they both - they both helped each other. They helped each other in everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Tell me about the circus you went to see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well it was someone called Clarks, I think it was called Clarks and - they
 had a baby on show, a baby - it was a - it wasn't a nice baby, what they call a - unnatural kind of child, and me father had forbidden us -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 A natural child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, it was unnatural. There was something wrong with it. Well they used to let them - 
freak of nature they called it. And they had it in a big glass case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 It was dead?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes, oh yes, it was preserved. So my father - knew about this and he'd forbidden us to go. And that's why he punished me by sending me upstairs you see because I didn't w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8474979\charrsid10309615 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 nt - It was a real baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But it was deformed - it had two heads?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes. And my father had forbidden us to go because there was a circus on you see. But I went and I flew home. I was terrified. Yes. I was only twelve years old then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were there a lot of people in watching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes, it was full. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 It was just in a box?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 It was in a glass case. I remember that now. But I remember flying almost terrified.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you just walked round it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Walked round, after the cir
cus everybody walked round to see - to look at this babe. But they wouldn't allow that today you know. Freak of nature. And I wanted to see this freak of nature. And I got - into trouble - a thing I remember quite well. Then before I left school there was
 
to be a social and we had to pay tuppence. Used to get a small pie and a cup of tea and then we could dance after. For all those as were leaving school. So - I was going that year so mother said I could have me best dress, have a white dress. So she put m
e
 this white dress on, I had beautiful hair, I could sit on my plaits, its true, I used to sit on them and they made me nice, father put me some clean shoes on. So I noticed my mother, she'd been cooking some beetroot, and left it on the dresser to cool, s
h
e hadn't put vinegar on. And how, I thought - I was a little pasty looking thing, I thought, ooh I wish I had red cheeks. So I said to mother, I'll go out the back way. I'm meeting Maggie. She said, all right. And she said, come straight home after. I sai
d
, yes. So - as I was going out with this - oh I was nice - going out I got a piece of this beetroot and I rubbed me cheeks with it. I thought, I'll have red cheeks too. When I got to the school Miss Winn was the teacher, she said, Florrie, has your mother
 
seen you? I said, yes. I said, she's got me ready. She said, where'd you get your rouge from? I said, it isn't rouge Miss Winn. Oh Florrie, she said, I'm surprised at you telling a lie, She said, your father. I said, it isn't rouge. She said, well take my
 towel and soap and go and wash it off. Which I did and when I came back no, she said, it isn't rouge. I said it was beetroot. So she had a good laugh and she gave me sixpence.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What age did you start school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I started school at five. I left at f
ourteen. Yes. Because I was too small to leave at thirteen. It was thirteen and as I was too small mother let me go twelve months extra. You could do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you first started at five did you go morning and afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I went all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What times did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 From nine 'til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How long did you have for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Just an hour and a half like they have now. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You came home to your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 We all came home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was it far away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No, not five minutes from where - King Street to Church Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 We all went on with each other - we went - the eldest looked after the young ones. As one started work see, we looked after each other.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What kind of a school was it, was it a church schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 It was a Catholic school. Catholic school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you went to the same school all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 All of us went to the same school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You were always at the same school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Always the same school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 It was a Farnworth school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 A Farnworth school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What was the name of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 . I went to St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
 church sixty years before I came here. And the Father - Father came to stay with me when they opened this home because I'd been a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 parishioner}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  sixty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you always went to St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Always to St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Gorgeous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  - all the family. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I - I liked going to school very much but I didn't learn enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I always wanted to learn more. But we were too poor to be sent anywhere else. I liked school. And I liked them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you like the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, and I loved the teachers. They were all kind to us, yes. I only got the cane once in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you get the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I got the cane - what did I get that cane for? Oh, I'll tell you now listen, don't put this down. The teacher sent me for some }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Beecham's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  Pills. Used to sell them in little packets, threepence a packet. So she said would I go to the chemis
t shop and bring her these pills. Well in the meantime she'd be doing our homework paper and I'd done my wrong. So when I came back I gave her the pills so she said I hadn't done the - the work that I ought to have done so she give me the cane. So I just 
said, there Mrs Sullivan I won't bring you anymore }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Beecham's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  Pills.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you get punished for generally though as children, did they punish the girls the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, the boys and girls were separate, the boys upstairs and the girls 
were down. But - they were - it wasn't a school they punished children a lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember the things you were punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I wasn't punished any more - any time that I remember, only that once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember anyone else being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I have seen girls caned. For being late. For being untidy. Or not doing their sums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you know what they emphasized as important when you were a child in schools, was it punctuality or manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Punctuality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Punctuality. And - being honest, truthful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did your parents take an interest in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes. As I - my father sometimes took us to school, to see how we were getting on. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did he see the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And saw - spoke to the teachers, yes. Very friendly with them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did the children in St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  all come from the same type of home as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Some children used to come from Hollins Home. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8474979\charrsid10309615 Work}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 house. Now those children were pathetic, all their hair was cropped and they had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They used to come to St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes. The Catholic ones, and they had thick clogs and thick - thick caps and all their hair was - almost shaved off. Now, they were something apart. They could tell - we could tell there was something different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You mean they were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Like they always looked something different than us. They were always at one side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You mean they didn't join in the games or they were left out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I think my
self they felt it. They felt it. But the teachers didn't punish them but they always were at one side. And I think those children felt it. Because they were dressed all in one uniform, a poor uniform and they had their hair all - cropped, you know, just l
ike - boys -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10309615  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 (showed).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you ever make friends with any of them and hear about their life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, I didn't because really I was too young to understand, I would understand now, but we didn't understand. We didn't know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You didn't know they were workhouse children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes, we knew they were workhouse children but we didn't bother with them because we didn't understand what those children were feeling, we didn't know, we had a good mother and father, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were there ever any children left out of things in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Not at all really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember the teachers singling out certain people for special attention?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I'll tell you what I do remember like that as I say about learning. I was very quick at a lot of t
hings, I never missed a class. But I always remember those - their parents were - teachers and they had a good job. Now those were the children that always won the scholarships. Well, teachers or their father had a good position somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Why do you think this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Because I think because their parents could keep them going, they had to pay those days you see to be educated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have to pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, we didn't, not at St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  but if they got a scholarship they went to Mount St Jos
ephs, they had to pay so much because my niece won one and her father had to pay for her. Well I longed to go but my mother and father was too poor, they couldn't have us going there you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You would have stayed on if you could have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, if I could, yes I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you think you benefited from your education though?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Oh yes. Yes, I think - I think myself - children those days, they were good writers and good spellers and I think they were quick at their sums. And I used to lik
e history and geography. I think myself today there's a smattering of this and a smattering of that and they like - they just pick anything up and they don't they don't retain what they've learned like we did. I think if we'd had the chance of what they h
ave today we'd have made a better show of it. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You have regrets then that you didn't go on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I have regrets that we were poor. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But you still felt you got some benefit from it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have gangs or groups in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
No. No. No. No. Always in the concerts together and - I was always in the concerts and used to sing and go on the stage. But the poor workhouse children had to go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They were never included?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They were never in the - in the concerts or the plays or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But did the teachers treat them exactly the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well they're - they're - under the council, the churches had nothing to say about it you see. They had what they call a mother, bringing them and taking them back you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have any part time education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I went to night school. Night school at St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 . You could go - they could go at seven o'clock 'til eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I used to learn sewing. And - cooking. Coo
k and sewing and - I - work you know on canvas. Embroidery. I can do that now. But I always liked sewing because I used to watch mother you see, but she never she would put us to it because she said it was a hard life sewing for other people. She didn't w
ant us to have that hard life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 While you were at school did you have a part time job to earn money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What was your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Just going in the mill to learn weaving with my sister at fourteen. And I worked in the mill thirt
y-six years when I went to hand sew after the war. After the second war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did you get your first job in the mill then, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Through my - my sisters all went. And they got - they got - got each other on you see. And the manager kne
w us and he knew that we were steady workers so we all got jobs under the same manager. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember what hours you worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, when I started work at the first, they started six o'clock. And - then they had an hour breakfast. Half an h
our for breakfast and we started again at half past eight 'til half past twelve. Used to go home for dinner then we used to have to work 'til half past five at night. Then I'd only be there about twelve month because the first world war broke out. And the
n they put the hours less you see. So - really I had a better time than me elder sisters, and I got - got more money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember your first wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes. I remember giving mother me half crown. Because I went to learn that was all. Then I go
t five shillings - then I was to get two looms, then you got two then you got four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You always gave the full half crown to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, always gave - the full half crown, I'd have got - that half crown she used to give us tuppence back. And
 every year we got older 'til we got about twenty-one she used to give us penny in the shilling. And we used to have to buy our own gloves out of that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you get any holidays with pay in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I mean before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did you feel about the wage, did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well we were too young to realize you see, we were - we were really too young to realize the hard life we were having you see. It was only through the war tha
t we got wakened up. People got better wages and they started going further a field and learning things. They got better wages, see, so - I think that - that in itself got poor people out of a hut, and it made them think more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you work Saturdays in that job or Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh no. I only remember working Saturdays for a few months, but after that we'd Saturdays off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember how your employer treated you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well - it wasn't the employer, it was the manager at first, he was a very s
trict severe man. He was rather a cruel man in some ways, he didn't understand many people. But I got through all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How was he cruel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, in many ways he used to watch and see if you let a little thing drop and he used to pick it up and th
en used to have them in the office and shout at them. If you was to make a mistake in the cloth used to have in the warehouse, used to get fined sixpence and that was taken out of your wage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Out of half a crown?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, not the half crown, when you 
got a loom of your own. Yes, they'd fine you sixpence. Yes. But they stopped all that during the first world war you see. Started giving us good wages. And then the second world war it was better still with the wages. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did you feel about him as a boss then, you didn't like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well I - well I didn't like him because I tell you when I was young - I was very happy natured and a - a girl and I always went out together and we used to be singing. I liked singing. And we used to be singing and
 he'd come through once when I was singing so I didn't take much notice of him, I went on, I was then about sixteen. So he sent in the office for me. And he said, I'm going to move you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Would you have preferred another job if you could have chosen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
That's why I went sewing. Yes, I wanted to get out of the mill, ah but you see with the war - with the war being on I couldn't, they wouldn't let me leave because they wanted - people in the mill.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you work at the same place all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
No. I came - I left - closed down in Farnworth, then I went to work in Busy with me sister seven years. 'Cos a special kind of weaving we did. Velvet and - they closed down there. Then I came and got a mill where Mr Hesketh was manager so I worked for hi
m ten years. And - as soon as the war was over I was off as soon as I could and went to a - a tailors shop doing all the hand sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have to serve an apprenticeship for your job in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Had to learn, oh yes, it was harder - it was 
harder learning weaving than sewing, it's more - brain work. Weaving. Oh yes, it's a very hard job. It was then
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were you in a trades union in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes. I was, and from sixteen. I was shop steward. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What years was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When I was at Prestwich's - about ten years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was this before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No, the last world war. The last - the last world war before I left I was shop steward there ten year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But before 1918 did you have a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Sixteen I joined the union. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you feel that there was a division of interest amongst the workers that you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. There was. Some of them - would leave it all to you. They'd c
ome to you with their troubles and ask you to go to see if they'd put them right. And when you asked them to be there they weren't there. They stayed away then and you had to face it all on your own. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What kind of trouble -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 This is before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, no, I don't remember - no, I wasn't shop steward, I was to young. I'm talking about the latter end of the war, this second war.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You don't remember any division of interest then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember if the employers and workers had the same interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Employers, yes, they did use the workers for their own ends those days. They got as much out of you for as little as possible. Now today it's gone the other length hasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But you felt then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They weren't giving us what we were worth. They didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you think there was a big difference between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh - oh yes, I should think so. And I'll tell you for why. When I became a shop steward the last world war I became a - had such a -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Before 1918 when you were a girl do you remember a big difference between craftsmen and other people when you first started in the mill, say between the weavers and the ordinary labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I tell you what I did not
ice, if you were a weaver you was considered high up but if you worked in the, what they call the cardroom, a little doffer and that, oh you was down below. They treated you different and they even couldn't - their boss or - they had a tap of their own to
 make their tea and the weavers had their own place to make their tea. There's that difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember any other difference between the two, in their standard of living or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I have - odd ones - I have noticed the w
eavers seem to be the better dressed and came from a different type of home than the other side, a lot of poverty those days. Yes, a lot of poverty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you think full time work changed your attitude to life in any way, when you went to work do you think you suddenly felt grown up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, I was sad because I had to go to work because I liked school. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes. We always got a present. Yes, only a small one, we always got 
a present. And we had a bit extra for tea. Mother used to make a cake and jelly - that was - no, we didn't have any visitors 'cos we had enough - we couldn't - we had a lot of our family, very seldom had visitors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What about Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well 
Christmas Day was the happiest day of the year. And mother always made a big Christmas pudding and - a nice dinner, turkey and everything else and me father used to come out with the Christmas spirit and we used to have a branch of holly and he used to ha
ve little drop of brandy in a glass and he used to set fire to the holly and pour the brandy over it. Remember that quite plain. Yes. We had a lovely Christmas Day and all had a present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What else did you do on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Sang - father used to play the piano and - play the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 accordion}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  and we used to be singing quite happy and we used to have all ways a white pinafore on mother had made with lace round. Tied at the back with a bow. We got presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you came down in turn for your stockings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. I got a doll at ten years old. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did your parents play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Father did because mother was always busy on the machine. But me father used to play - take a big interest in us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 We had books, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember your mother or father reading and did they read aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. My mother used to read out loud for us but my father - liked politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He was interested in politics was he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Always interested in politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did he discuss it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
And he used to discuss it with mother because I always remember my father saying to my mother, Lucy, there's going to be a - a big war. She said, how do you know James? H
e said, well, he said, I can tell what's coming he said. Perhaps not just now but the children will see it, he said, I don't think I will, because he was ill. He said, there's going to be a terrible war. And two years after the first world war }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 broke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did he take part in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He - he - he was a Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did he ever help in an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He helped in the - election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You remember him working for that? Did your mother take part in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No. She was too busy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did she have any views on politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She never vote - she never - told us what her views were but I do know she was a Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And your father was a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 My father was a - a dead Conservative. I think myself, that to be, I used to say to my mother, well I think you're a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Liberal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
, my father's a - we called them Tories then. She said, well you know the Tories called Tories because they used to persecute the Catholics in the old times. But mother used to say, that's nothing to do 
with us now. She said, all the Catholics are mostly Liberals on account of that but all that business went out with Queen Victoria, she were emancipated and she lifted people up and I think all the bitterness of religion and politics she did good there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember any persecution of Catholics in Farnworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No. Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you think your father felt that he had to vote a certain way or he would lose his job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, no, I think, no, I think he liked Conservatives, they always we
re a Conservative and I don't think he would ever have been anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You remember him voting at a general election do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes. He used to go with big blue rosette on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You never felt he was under any pressure to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. Mother - mother used to say to us, now if ever you're in company and start }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 talking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
 - leave politics and religion out of your conversation. There's more enemies made through those two things than anything else in the world. Yes. But I can never remember any - any persecution of any sort really. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You felt you could have got somewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, yes. I liked going to school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you ever attend a funeral in the family, anything you can tell me about a funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, in my family. I've stood beside eight death beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 My little brother died and I went to his funeral. He was nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was this before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 That was 1910 I think, 1910, my father died 1912. And - I remember going to Joseph's funeral and that wer
e the first one I ever attended and then me father died and I went to his.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Can you tell me about the funeral who attended them and what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You all had to wear black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I wore a black - black hat but mother wouldn't let us we
ar black clothes, we had to have black armband, a band on our arm. We went to father's funeral, wouldn't let us have black on. She let us wear black hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you had a mass?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And my brother - didn't have mass then. Well you can have one now but 
you see we didn't have those because we didn't have requiem mass then and we buried him in the afternoon and we all went and there's - four carriages with plumes on, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15680338\charrsid10309615 Belgian}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  horses, yes, it was lovely. And my father's aunt was an undertaker named Heywood a
nd I think sometimes that's why my father never became a Catholic on account of my - it - because there was a lot of trouble when he married my father - my mother over religion, they didn't want him to marry my mother because she was a Catholic and he was
 the only child and there was money and my father didn't get a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Because he'd married a Catholic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Because he married and because he was buried a Catholic and I think that was the reason why he never would become a Catholic while he lived. But he died a Catholic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have a lot of relatives living nearby and did you see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
In Bolton - in Bolton we had two cousins and in Heywood and had this aunt one of me uncles sisters called - but she came from, no, she was an undertaker - 
she buried him. She bought his coffin, had his coffin made and everything and she was the only one that came near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you see them as children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 It - it was the religion that broke up the family. Even his own father turned against him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Suppose your mother was ill who used to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Mother never had - she - she really didn't need much help, only when the babies were born. (Mother was never ill).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who helped her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And my father used to do a lot for her. My
 father was a - a right hand man. And she didn't need help only she had sisters that used to come and help her 'cos they had families of their own but my father's family rejected them all together. Because of religion, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you never see them as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Only two cousins came after he was - the day after he was buried and had been to the cemetery to see where he was buried. And because he was buried on the Catholic ground they said to my mother, we can't help you Lucy. You know why. Mother s
aid, yes, she said, and I don't want any help. You haven't helped up to now, I'll manage, please God I'll manage. And that were the last time I saw them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How old would your mother be when your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh she'd be - father was fifty-four and she was about the same age, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And she had to take in sewing to bring you up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And she take in sewing, yes, to. Then we had to take up where she left off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did your mother and father have a lot of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. They had good neighbours. Good friends and neighbours, yes. My father was well liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes. Everybody was welcome at weekend. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you visit them a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, we didn't go out visiting much but they used to come to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They used to come to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, yes. Until father -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 For a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 
Or my father could play the piano, used to have evenings together and me eldest sister was in the opera society and we used to have nice evenings at ni
ght you know learning all the opera songs and - and father Whitman what was over the opera used to come and have a nice night you know, tea in them, have a nice time.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 This was how they made their amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Made - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Could friends come without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes. Oh - they just called in - when they wanted. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Can you tell me if your mother had friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well she had because, you see, she went to the church and church meetings and she went to the 
Ladies - the Ladies Guild and she sewed for the bazaars and therefore she helped at the parties therefore she had a lot of friends. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Your father never drank at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. Never touched it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Never went out on his own or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No. Always with me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where did they go to when they went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well I think they - mostly they used to go to the concerts and the operas and - at school and - and church concerts, they was always together. They never went to the pictures. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did they go out visiting friends and relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Occasionally. When they had time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And they used to take you with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes, the youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 So your mother did go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh she got out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But your father never went out on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He didn't go out on his own, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When he came home from work in the evenings how many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When he came home from work he had a lot of clerical work to do. Dad used to l
eave that 'til we'd all got in bed at night. So - so that used to take a lot of his time up. Then he had this other side line, used to go out after and pick some money up you know, when he'd sold his goods and that. And that's way we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But apart from that he would always stay in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Always stay - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When your mum and dad }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 weren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  doing their work how did they spend their spare time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, they hadn't much really. I always remembered them spending their time with us. Always with us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Your father didn't take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Or bet or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Cricket. He used to like watching cricket matches because he's taken us to watch the cricket. He loved watching cricket matches. Yes. I've been with him often to watch cricket matches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And he never drank or went to a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, never went in a public house in his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember if they belonged to any savings clubs like savings clubs or boot clubs or sick clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well - the only place 
my mother put anything was in the Co-op. Society. She was like - in the Co-op, she was a member of the co-op. Now, used to get a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 dividend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 , now that's my mother's savings bank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Didn't they belong to insurance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh the Royal - we're all in the Roya
l Liver you know. Everyone of us, my father entered us as soon as we were born. And when I went to draw my mother's insurance money, my sister wasn't well enough to go and I went the man said, will you wait a minute? So he brought the head manager and sho
wed me father's name in the big book where he'd entered us all. He said, what a coincidence. I said, that's my father's name. He said, yes. He said, but it's very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 seldom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  it happens, yes. He said, your father entered you all at birth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
No, we had friends but we didn't neighbour much. But friends and relatives, yes. Mother's relatives. And me mother used to go out on the market Saturday with father with two big shopping bags and the el
der ones used to have to go with them and help them to carry the grocery for the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you ever do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I was just a little one, I got out of a lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did your father ever take you out on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes, he used to take us
 walk all round - it was all farm land round here once, used to take us all round here, round Hollins Home, that was where the children was that was - used to watch the cricket matches. Used to call at the farm and give us a glass of milk and fetch us hom
e. Yes. While mother got on with her sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you go away for Bank holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, no, I don't think we ever got away like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. They never had enough money. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you do on Saturdays when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well Saturday I don't think we did much, only play. We'd play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where did you play? Did you play in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, not in the street because we lived near a - a - undertaker's and she had a lot of ground at the back, and used to let us play there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 My brothers and sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Not neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No, always together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh, I liked me brothers. I loved me brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was there anyone you sere specially close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I loved him more than anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Which one was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 My brothers that got killed in the war. We always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Why did you love him more do you think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I don't know, but I'd a - I'd great affection for him. More than any of them. We were always together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember the games you played as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Hopscotch and - they had a little tucker shop and used to run across and guess what was in the window an come ba
ck to see if the other could find it and - we used to stop in the house and play certain games with initials you know, finding what was on the wall with certain letters and that's the way we used to spend our time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were you allowed to get dirty?
