No. Not dirty - well to - we were allowed to get soiled but not dirty, as soon as we came in we had to wash our hands and face and we had to wash our feet every night before we went to bed. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were you allowed to play with anyone you wanted or were there certain children your parents didn't like you to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh certain children we hadn't to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8474979\charrsid10309615 bother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Because they're rough. Me father wasn't a rough man. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 
He was very, very particular who we played with. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well we used to go to - the - the Guilds, what they called the Ladies Guild, the children of Mary and joined in the social life there at church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you were at school did you have any hobbies, did you keep pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
No, we didn't have pets because neither mother and father liked cats and dogs. But we liked birds. Me father had canaries. He loved birds, yes. Used to sing, whistle, oh he loved birds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you do for your hobbies as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I liked - I used to always making dolls clothes. Yes. Painting and sewing little bits of things you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you go for walks or bicycling?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I had no bicycle. Went for long walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No sports, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you were at school did you go to theatres or music halls or cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 We went to the cinema occasionally but mother would never let us go to a theatre or music hall, she was always afraid of a fire. Always d
readed a fire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I wonder why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
I don't know. Sometime I think she cared for us too much. You can do you know, you can be too sheltered and then when you come to face the world you get a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 shock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 . I think I found that out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You think you were too sheltered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes, because I'll tell you for why. When I came here and all the family had gone and - I thought well this is the end. I'm all left alone and - I've heard people talk and I've read things, I've thought, well what a sheltered life we'v
e had. And I thought all the world had come to an end when I had to break my home up and come here after I lost my sister. I thought, well, if you're brought up and you - you can rough it a little, you can go about - you don't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 suffer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  the same as what you do having sheltered life. You understand? You can be too sheltered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you think you were too sheltered as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 To a certain extent. We weren't brought up rough and I think myself my father was too gentle. He wasn't - he was kind and gentle 
I think that's how he made us too sheltered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You loved your father obviously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh loved father, yes, we all loved me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. And father, mother was always busy. She loved us but she hadn't time to pet us. Me fathe
r did. Yes. Did the petting, yes. Yes. But I feel my life has had it's nice side and I've been very happy. Lots of times I've been very happy with me family. And I've missed them. I have, I've missed them. Well thank God me nieces and nephews never leave 
me alone, they're always someone coming.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were you allowed to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Or did they think it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 
Mother wasn't narrow minded, nor father, narrow minded about games. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Play as often - as long as we were happy it didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They didn't mind at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did they think it was wrong to work on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh they didn't do any work on Sunday. Didn't do any work on Sunday, just the washing up. Weren't allowed to any - any - crocheting or k
nitting or - cleaning - everything had to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You weren't allowed to go out and play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, you could play games but no work - no - no work. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you go on any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. We went to - we went to Blackpool in coaches. Yes, went to Blackpool - father used to take us in coaches and - went to Wales, Holy}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
ell. Yes. Southport. Oh we used to go all the school trips, taking the children. Yes, we used to go, yes. You know, cost about half a crown for the whole day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you belong to the choir at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I was in the choir 'til I was sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did they have any social life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But they had - yes, but they used to be all be together, they didn't keep the choir separate. Used to all go together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What other social activities did you have in your church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well they had an opera society, there was three of our family in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 At the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. A lovely opera society and a dramatic society. And we had - \{ILLEGI BLE\} socials, oh and whis
t drives. I used to attend them all. Yes. All of those. Parties. Mother used to - do all the cutting up with all the other ladies behind the scenes you know. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have a temperance club at your church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They have, yes, but only for men. No women allowed in there at St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 
Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 , yes. But no women allowed then, only men. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was your father in it do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Me father, no. Not in any club, no. Never - to go anywhere -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You never heard anything about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. They wouldn't tolerate drink in any shape a form no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Was grace said at meals in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes. Yes, every time we sat down, yes. Yes. Yes, before and after meals. Yes. I remember once - I once got - got up - brothers - he was having porridge for his br
eakfast 'cos she couldn't give us anything else that day. And he said - well come on Joseph, what do you say before you leave the table? He said, have I to say prayers for porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have family prayers at night too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes, we had to kne
el down before we went up stairs and say a few prayers before mother's knee. And my father used to sing a little - he used to take us all upstairs and used to separate in the rooms, we had to go to different - and we used to sing that - There are four ang
e
ls round my bed, every corner an angel spreads. One to sing, one to pray and two to carry my soul away. And I said, oh I don't want anyone to carry my soul away. You don't - you don't find anything like that now do you. My father were a nice singer. But m
y elder sister had a beautiful voice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you used to sing this at night when you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Used to sing - something different every night you know. At the top of the stairs so we could all hear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 So that you were between the two rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes, yes. What a sheltered life we had had.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. We had only so much. Penny shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you were a child at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes, penny, that's all. On Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Used to go on the market and buy ice cream.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Always ice cream?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes, yes, nearly always ice cream, ice cream. And the fair mother used to give us tuppence or threepence then each. When the fair was on, you know, used to come back and we use
d to fetch mother and father, spend all our money on coconuts and something for mother and father, didn't spend it on ourselves. Yes. Or a water melon - a water melon, and mother thought we were giving her the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 If you bought her a watermelon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you went to work you still lived at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you think going to work changed your attitude towards your brothers and sisters and your parents in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I think you have a tendency to - want to go a bit on 
your own and - like coming back to them but they like to find their own friends. You find a lot of friends that you work with. We used to like - like coming home but you used to want a friend of your own when you started work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You made new friends at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes, I made new friends at work, yes, and fetched them home and you used to think, well, I'm getting too old now to have this tacked onto me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you do when you were in your teens and working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh I used to go dancing in the club hall and dancing in the school. Go to our friends, we used to have American }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 tea parties}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  in each others house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You started something, you had to take something and used to put it all together and used to have a party and used to
 pay sixpence beside and we used to give that to the church and used to - Mary had a piano and she used remove all the furniture, we used to have a dance in the front room. Used to make American teaparty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you meet new friends from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Well - but mostly from church. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did your parents like to meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes, everybody was welcome. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have to be in at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, had to be in, yes. All in b
y ten. And those - if they started keeping company they were allowed out a little bit longer. But they had to tell me mother where they were going. So they new where they were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you could bring them home when you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you have any new hobbies or anything then, how did you spend your spare time part from dancing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well - there wasn't really much spare time with working for your living, coming home, going to night school sometimes and going to socials really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were you interested in politics yourself as you grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, never have been, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You still went to church of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. And the priest brings the Holy communion once a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you first started work did you still continue at church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh I never left church. I went for sixty years 'til I came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you still keep up Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They - no, the priest comes to me now because I can't there you see, now, I can't walk so far. I have to keep sitting down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But when you were young you still kept it up did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes, all of us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You still kept up Sunday school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes. 'Til I was - oh, I should say about forty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You went dancing in the evenings as you were growing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
That - well it was far different. I think myself we were far happier. We used to go to these social evenings and these dances in the hall and then used to have a guild, and go there and they used to have a special night for their dancing, there
 was always a night for something, always. Belonged to the church you see. Used to help the church a lot. Used to find a lot of pleasure in doing that. We never used to think about - going out, going mad or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 If anybody did anything that people disapproved of, say a woman or a man that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8474979\charrsid10309615 neighbours}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
 didn't approve of, do you remember how they showed their disapproval, do you ever remember them singing loud songs or banging cans or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Nothing like that, no. Oh no. Never heard - never anything like that. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class or group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And can you tell me what the different ones were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well, well there was I was - not at - when I left school we had to go to work and some of these girls that had won scholarships and got on and had a good education they'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8474979\charrsid10309615 broke}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  away from us. Yes. They went on their
 own, they didn't seem to - to come to us like they used to do before they went to these high school, they bake away. I noticed that there was some kind of distinction. Between the girls who went to a high schools and those that had to go out living - wor
king for a living.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And what people belonged to the same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 In your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I - I work - belong to the working class but the respectable working class, 
that have been brought up with a good mother and father. And taught how to behave ourselves. That's all I can say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You though of some people as being respectable and some as rough did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Now we weren't allowed to be - bothered with anyone
 that was rough and we weren't allowed to bother with anyone that was - had a fight or anything and we - weren't allowed to go down certain streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Which streets were these, somewhere in Farnworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Kent St, but don't put that down where mostly Irish people lived they were always fighting at weekends. Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8474979\charrsid10309615 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
 weren't allowed to go down that street. Even though we were working class, we were what you call a sheltered working class. We didn't know any of the wrong that those rough ones knew an
d we never heard of - immorality. We weren't allowed to hear it. That is to say we're sheltered. And I think it's a big shock to you when you get to know all these things later on in life. I think myself - lot of your social workers can get - broad minded
 - that's not been brought up as well as you. As being something different than you. Now perhaps if they'd have had the chance that we'd have had they'd have been better than us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you think your mother ever felt that she belonged to a certain class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
No, I don't think she did but I think my father did. Well - I think he belonged to the work - to the middle class, but he never would talk about his family 'cos they rejected him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Why do you think your father felt this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Because he always s
eemed something above the ordinary to us. We always seemed - what shall I say - nice. He didn't like anything that wasn't nice. Liked us to behave ourself and he wasn't rough, he was gentle.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember any rough families round about and what they were like and what their homes were like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well, I have been in one or two from school they've taken me to their homes and they have had a very rough outlook. A rough table. No cloth on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How would the house be furnished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Very very poor. N
ot like ours. Though we weren't well-to-do, but we always had a nice clean home and always dressed nice. Our mother would even made clothes or other women's children so they'd have something to walk in the Whit walk with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You always took part in the Whit Walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes. My mother's made the poor - the poor children she's made them sets of frocks and knickers to walk in so they wouldn't feel out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Where would she get the material from to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Oh used to buy them at Rosser's, in a sh
op called Rosser's in Market Street and she used to pay for all - yes - for all of the children, they knew her quite well because she used to sew for them, she used to make shirts for them to sell in the shop, and another place called Walworth\rquote 
s in Bradford Street. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
And she used to get all her materials from there. Mother used to get them cheap sometime. Now she saw a little child there very poor, and no clothes and she'd say, she can't walk mother, she's no dress. And she'd say, oh she'll walk. And mother s
ent for them and made them little white dresses. Yes. I've been told by a - a friend of - the woman that lives round here and she knew me. I say, I'll always remember your mother's kindness to us. We've walked with the Whit Walk when we couldn't have walk
ed at all, through your mother. That were the type of mother I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She was lovely wasn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes she was. Yes. And it's a good memory to have. I think it's awful to have poor parents. Unkind parents, I think it's dreadful. I think - as you grow
 older that love comes back. It's come back to me in many ways, it's come back through my nieces and through their children and they bring me all presents, I feel like Queen Victoria Christmas Day waiting for me presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You mean this love extends right through a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes. I - yes, it all comes back. I don't think any unkindness goes and - unnoticed - even if you have to wait years for it, it comes back to you in different way. Even the love that you've given comes back to you many ways as yo
u grow older. I've found that out with my own nieces and nephews and their children they'd never left me. And they always say I'm in need of anything. And I think that's nice. I think it's nice to be able -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You felt it came back to your mother too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes it did. Yes. And we nursed her fourteen years, we never would let her go to hospital. Yes. Fourteen long weary years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When did she die, you say she was fifty-four when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She was fifty-four when - no, mother was eighty when she d
ied and father was fifty-four. Yes. And she had her own teeth. She'd just bought the dentist twice to have two teeth out. She had her teeth and she could see. She had a clever brain. But she was helpless from the waist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember any other class of people apart from working class or middle class, do you remember any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes, I remember - two of his cousins coming once. And a real - they looked like two real ladies. And I remember them asking father and take mother and us to her tea and we went
 and they had a beautiful home and all I can remember - it was up Didscough because I was only three or four. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Didscough, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
And they had property and all I remember is going to this big house and Amelia, my sister, was going and she was playing the piano
 for us. And I - always have that in my mind and that was the only time that I remember ever seeing my father's relatives, his own father cast him on the street. Just because he married my mother - a Catholic, see. But he was a choirmaster the - at the ch
u
rch where he went and I think - people used to be very narrow minded at one time and bigoted about religion didn't they. Oh yes, and I think myself that was it. I think me father really did belong to the middle class and it showed in many ways. It showed 
in the way he cared for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember any upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Now that was the only time I - I remember seeing anyone well-to-do when I went with my mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember being brought up to treat some people differently from others, were you ever told to curtsey or show respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No. No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember anyone being called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember your mother or father being referred to or treated in this way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. I don't but everyone seemed to love my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people and why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I think the district where we lived - well it was a nice district. We all seemed to be nice people that I remember
 of them. I don't remember any distinction whatever. No. Only like some went to a school - other school and they won scholarships and they broke away, they went to be teachers and they got - they go to the bigger house and that the way -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Your memories of distinction are all about education aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You don't remember anybody being specially important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Can you tell me about the shopkeepers, who did they mix with in the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Well - they didn't seem to mix with anyone in particular because they went to the same shops really.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well the clergy - they were very - they came to our house a lot. Nearly every day of the week one or two'd come 'cos I think they liked watching the c
hildren and we were churchgoers and we worked hard for the church and my mother was a nice good woman so I think that drew them to us more and then my father being - loved music and my sister being in the opera I think that's the way they used to come to 
our house a lot more than perhaps they went to someone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who do you think the teachers mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well the teachers, I always get on with the teachers, every one of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who do you think they mixed with socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well - what I know of St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  teachers, they didn't pick and choose much. They treated all the children alike, only those poor little workhouse children. They were kept apart, I always - that stood out in my memory. They were always on the side.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did they look well fed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Oh they looked well fed but they were - dressed coarse you know and their hair was cropped and - were made to feel something apart really. But I loved the teachers. They were all nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who do you think the teachers mixed with when they finished school though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well the teachers seemed to - to do a lot for us after school hours. Yes. Always smoothing going on, socials, dances. Teaching us. Going to school after school hours and showing us how to do things. We used to go to one teache
r's house for music - you know to sing, the choir, she used to play the organ and they had a - a rabbit and soon as you got in this front room they used to learn the singing she used to say, now listen. And as soon as she's played a few notes there's scra
tching on the door. The rabbit wants to come in. And it was stood like that all the time - she was called Mrs Kehoe and I - she used to teach us how to sing in the choir. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What about employers when you first stated work, who would your manager mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well, he was a man that nobody liked, he wouldn't mix with anyone. And they always said he came from Germany. And he'd - four sons. But he was a tyrant, the manager. Everybody seemed afraid of him. And I've always remembered that man but I wasn
't under him very long before he died. But he was tyrant. Well then - then things changed - seemed to go to a lot better. But he was a very harsh man. You'd frightened to death making a mistake. It was. My eldest sister went into him once and said, do you
 know Mr Day, she said, you're only short of a whip. He said, do you know who you're speaking to? Yes, I'm speaking to you, she said, you can give me the sack if you like. He told her to go back to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How do you think he got away with it, were jobs very hard to come by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I think myself - poverty did a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You told me you'd seen a lot of poverty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, a lot of poverty in Farnworth too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Tell me about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well - I can't tell you much about the real poverty 'cos I didn't 
deal with a lot of the real poverty but I've seen the girls in school and I've seen some of the boys who've come with one shoe and one clog on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 -Because they hadn't a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10309615  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 
pair}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, they hadn't a pair. And they've had - their trousers torn. Well I - I noticed that. How we were kept apart from them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Who by - your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
By my - no, my mother and father. No, the teachers were very nice but we hadn't to deal with anybody that was rough. I think myself that's a big mistake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You were telling me they had to stay at work and put up with this man because of this poverty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Because a lot of poverty, they're frightened of losing their jobs you see. Because jobs weren't easy to get. Then the first world war broke out and it altered peoples lives completely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Do you think your mother and father had the same attitude to people in different classes, you said your father wouldn't let you deal with anybody rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Would this apply to mother too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Mother did
n't - she didn't - domineer us like - in her - in a way but she used to be - now tell me where you're going, who you're going with. And I'd be all right. But weren't to go anywhere unless we were told her who was going with and where we went. We weren't a
llowed to go out and please ourselves where we went or what we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
In the district where you lived did the people in the working class all have the same standard of living or did you think there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, they hadn't. No they ha
dn't, they all had different kinds of homes, some were rough some were nice, some were poor, some didn't care tuppence what became of the children. They always - you can go in different houses and see a difference in peoples ways. In life. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 I remember going
 in one house after school and they were called Kellen, they didn't live in - they lived a street further up, they were very very poor and they were some of the children that mother made dresses for and I remember the tea was ready and they had a big pan 
of - on the fender, potatoes in their jackets. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
And they had a white scrubbed table, no cloth on. No cloth on. And the children went and got a potato and sit at the table with no cloth on. Now I came home said to my mother. ooh, Kellens have no cloth on the 
table and they're eating potatoes out of a pan. I said, can we do that? Father said, no you can't. But I used to slip out many a time, I used to go to Kellen's I used to run out and go and knock on the door, can I have a potato please? Out of the pan. All
 that, you know, I remember all that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were some streets different to others in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well No - not in Farnworth, nearly - nearly all the streets were alike. They were all working class - kind of streets really, only Rawson Street which was an Irish. St \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 Darcy Rd, those were kind of middle class houses. Middle class houses. There's people there the professional class used to go there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you ever remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes I do. Real gentleman was Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Derbyshire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
 and he lived in - Bridgman Street. That was a nice street. And we used to go there and he kept a - he kept a jewelers and pawnbrokers shop and mother was friendly with his wife because she used to sew for them an
d bring to their house but he was a real gentleman but they were well-to-do. They'd come from a nice family. Really nice people. But they had a different kind of life to us. Yes, a lot of difference in their - the house and I say the house was bigger, the
y'd more money, the sons went to college. But still they made no difference to my mother and us, we were always welcome. Mother sewed for Mrs }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Derbyshire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 anyone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  being called a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I remember the headmistress at St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 , she was called Miss Kelly and she was a real born lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
She was beautiful and she never used to cane us and she - we loved to - misbehave ourselves and she'd help those that were down. She always watched the children and if she thoug
ht they were very very poor she used to help them. And when she left school - ooh, she had some beautiful presents the children bought her. She was a real little lady. And she lived 'til she was eighty. So I grew - as I grew up she saw me in the street on
ce, she said, she used to call me Florence - Florence, my word you have got in to be a young woman. Yes. She was a nice lady. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you were a child do you think there was a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, big distinction. O
h yes. Well I used to notice the labourer was a - usually kind of - rough type of man that went in the public houses and - perhaps beat his - perhaps beat his children and his wife. Now the craftsman, the joiners and - and all them that wanted - they had 
a
 nicer outlook on life and nicer kind of people. I noticed that when I was young. Yes. I was observant you know. I noticed that. You get a very rough kind of person - they don't care tuppence whether they - get out of the labouring classes or not. Now you
 get the other kind that try to get on and they do get on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you think it was possible to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I think it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you ever know anyone who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. But through winning scholarships. Always through edu
cation. And I think that's the greatest thing you can have, if you want to get on in the world, but get on in the proper manner, not be a snob. I think it's the best thing out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You've known people to get on through education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I - have known a lot of people get to the top if they've been educated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Have you known anyone go down in life before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No. No. I've seen them rise but never fall. Yes, seen them rise, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You were a Roman Catholic, do you remember seeing a difference
 between the people who went to church and the people who sent to Chapel, socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I - have - they've - gone to these churches }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8474979\charrsid10309615 because}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  so and so went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You're talking about the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Protestant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 The protestant church, I - I'm not bit
ter, I don't - all religions good to me - but you find people, they used to go to chapel and church because their bosses went and they wanted to see - wanted him to see them there so they could get rise in their work see. But as a Catholic you were bound 
to go to mass on Sunday, if you had to be a good Catholic, and it didn't make any difference to us who was there and who wasn't there as long as we were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you know any chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They - know a lot - my mother being dressmaker she'd c
ome into contact with all kinds of people and we had some good friends, non-Catholics. Some of my mother's best friends were those who weren't Catholics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you think of chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I liked a lot of them. I think they're nice. And I've 
found out as I've got older a lot of them real Christians. They are. I don't think - I think religions something - it doesn't make you it's what you are to begin with. I think it is. I've had had a lot of non-Catholic friends. Good - friends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you never found any prejudice about being a Catholic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 I've never had no prejudices at all. No. No. And I've had some good friends that's non-Catholics. And they still come to see me here.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember any class of people when you were young who considered themselves superior to other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes. I did. A few. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What types were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well they were people that - they got a scholarship, their father got good jobs and their fathers became managers in mill therefore they got into
 bigger houses and they went away and I noticed them when we were at socials, they all kept to one side and - you noticed all those kind of things, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you were a child was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh always rented, never owned a house, we always rented, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did you ever see anything of your landlord and what did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes, we had - we had some nice ones. We had some nice - and the nicest landlord we had was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Prestoll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  Street. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember seeing a policeman round your district when you were a child and what did you think of him and how he treated the people?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did your mother ever say, if you're naughty I'll tell the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. Never. No. No. No, I don't - we saw very - very few policemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You don't remember how he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
No. Of course we never came in contact with a policeman. Used to see them in Market Street when we passed the police station going to school but - they never come near the house. They had no need really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And you don't know how he treated the people at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. No. Oh we never came in contact with a policeman, we very seldom saw them coming down the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What about when there were fights, you said there were Irish Streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Oh those were in the streets further on. Kent Street. Oh that was a terrible street. They were always there - they always seemed to be passing their time on there therefore we had to keep away. Always on there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Why was this a terrible street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 
Because you see I think they were mostly Irish immigrants and they all liked beer, they all went out and they'd come back and their children would all be half dressed and the wives would have no money to buy f
ood but still their husbands'd go out drinking. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And then start fighting. Then the policeman had to go there. You see, we got none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 And the policeman would sort the fights out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 The policeman would start with his baton then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Have you seen this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No. but I've heard it about it 'cos the girls have told us at school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 He would go in and separate them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Would separate them, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you feel that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 They had a hard struggle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well - we did our best for them like they did for us, we never had no - we had no hard feelings towards them because we knew they were doing their best for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did they ever have to go to anyone for help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
No. Never. We've never gone through that. No, never had to do that. No. You see, with their being - mind you, I know we were poor but we were respectable poor. Mother kept us well dressed and well fed and people didn't know how poor we wer
e. Yes. Never - we never asked - me mother never asked for help. No. We were forbidden to go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You were telling me the windows would be all plastered up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Lot - a lot - a lot of them were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Plastered up with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Rugs or anything you could get. 'Til they have to put in again 'til they were broken again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did they get broken?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Perhaps throwing bottles or anything like that or bricks \{BLANK\} Salvation Army daren't go down. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 It was too rough for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Too rough. 
Now that's why I'm telling you my father protected us, we were sheltered from all that, never would let us come in contact with it and we used to - I used to feel delighted if I could away in to watch it. If I could just sneak away and watch it. And I use
d to run home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Did any of the children come to St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, most of them did with being Irish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Were they left out of things do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, the teachers were very kind to them but - they were poor. Poorly dressed, poorly fed. Y
es. And probably some of them thought we were snobs and we were as poor as them but we didn't show it. They showed it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Can you describe your childhood in Farnworth to me, Farnworth as the place that you knew and the people in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well 
I think Farnworth's been a very nice place to live in. I've always liked it and if I had a lot of money left me today I wouldn't leave Farnworth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But as a child you said there was poverty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 But there's been a lot of poverty, a lot of poverty that we didn't see and a lot of hidden poverty.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Looking back to your childhood some people think of it as the good old days }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8474979\charrsid10309615 some}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  think of it as the good old days, what did you feel about your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Well I think myself they were really days as 
far as my childhood was concerned. But bad days as afar as the money was concerned. You longed for things that you couldn't have. Now today they don't have that longing because they have them put into their hands haven't they. If I could have the chance t
h
at some of them have today I would have been - well I would have been happy. I think I would have liked to have been a teacher, something like that. 'Cos I've been interested in education but I've never had the chance to be educated. What brains I have I'
ve kept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Have you any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well - not being able to - have a better life - a better way of life I should say. They all, when I watch the television I thank God I have had the life that I've had. Because there's a lot wors
e off. There's a lot of - terrible poverty. I always when I get in bed at night I always say, thank God for what I have and what I can't have I'll have to do without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What was the part of your life you hated most, in the mill was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 In the mill. I didn't like it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Tell me why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
I didn't like the noise and the machinery, I didn't like the grinding and the - I didn't like it at all. And as soon as I had my chance I left. And I went into hand sewing and mother never would let us do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How old would you be then when you went into hand sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh I should be - about forty-nine. I went sewing and so I was happy then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you remember how much }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15225548\charrsid10309615 you started}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh started at - I started at the bottom because you had to do but I was quick getting up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You had to serve an apprenticeship for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Yes, but I was so quick with watching mother and being used to it you see I got up quickly in fact when I was fifty-seven they had to take me away, I dropped and they 
had to take me away. And when I was in hospital the manager sent me a letter to be quick and get better as I was going to be the head in that room over the others. And I'd only been there three years then. But I never had the chance to go back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you were in the mill though did you get on well with the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Yes, I liked the people. I liked -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You didn't like the manager?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, no. But I liked the people. Very nice, yes. And I used to help them, the young ones used to help the old o
nes. And with brothers and sisters there too I had to behave myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 When you were growing up in the family did the children all help each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes, we had to help - we had to help to dress each other and - see if the others were washed if 
they weren't properly washed, we used to take them back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You'd take the younger ones back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 We'd take the younger ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Tell me about your childhood and your brothers and sisters, what it was like, what you remember about it personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well - I think I've told you all I do remember really, about us being - all together. Having our hard times, our hardships and having a lot of happiness and best of all having a good mother and father. And growing up in a good home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 So poverty didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
And poverty didn't matter because it wasn't a grinding poverty and it wasn't a rough poverty. It was what you call a genteel poverty. Yes, nice - nice to be - happy and protected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How do you mean poverty, because you were well fed and well clothed weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Well I think poverty can be poor in many ways, you can be poor with being short of something that you want to get on. But you see other people getting without effort. There's something you wanted and being too big a family t
o get it, and mother wouldn't let one be better than the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 What do you remember as a child that you wanted badly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 To go to a school where - I've always wanted to go to a nice school and wear a uniform. Yes. It's strange that isn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Do you think your mother ever felt the poverty badly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Oh yes, I think she did. I think it hurt her when she couldn't - give us all we wanted. But she did her best. She always kept us in -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She never talked about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Sometimes she used to s
ay, I wish I could give you more. But she gave us love and she gave us always the best that she could give us. And I remember when she was dying what she said, she said, to my sister and I, sit down, she said - don't think I don't know the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8474979\charrsid10309615 sacrifice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615  you ha
ve made fore me. I do. And God will reward you one day. And she died that day. So that was nice. I always think well that was nice - nice ending to a nice life. She even thanked the doctor for all he done for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She never grumbled about her hard life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 She never grumbled and all the time she was in bed she never grumbled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You mean when she was young you never heard her grumble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 Never heard her, she used to say, God's Holy will be done. And through all - all that poverty and all her de
bt and that that she suffered she used to say, God's Holy will be done. There's a reason for everything. No, she was very very cheerful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 You would have thought that losing so many children would really have got her down wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 No, she wasn't - she wasn't bitter or anything. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5267124 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 How did your father take it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13245739 FA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
Father wouldn't - never rebelled. He never rebelled. No. I think I had one the father's - one of the nicest fathers one could wish to have. And I've stressed all that haven't I. Yes.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-461\li461\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid5267124 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9853094\charrsid10309615 
\par }}